# Implement src/main_wasm.ml: minimal command dispatch (help, version, status, agent, memory list, identity)

## Requirements

- Create `src/main_wasm.ml` as a standalone OCaml file with no Lwt, no SQLite, no cohttp, no mirage-crypto dependencies.
- Implement command dispatch via `Sys.argv` match:
  - `help` (or no args): print help text listing all available WASM commands.
  - `version`: print `"clawq {version}-wasm"`.
  - `status`: print build info (version, build mode, supported commands list).
  - `agent`: run a synchronous stdin→stdout single-turn loop: read one line from stdin, print a response line to stdout (LLM call deferred to future task; for now print `"[agent not yet connected to LLM in WASM mode]"`).
  - `memory list`: call `read_memory_md ()` (see T004) and print entries.
  - `identity`: read `AGENTS.md` from the current directory if it exists, print its contents; otherwise print a default identity stub.
  - `onboard`: delegate to the onboard template writer (see T005).
  - Any unknown command: print error to stderr and exit 1.
- No use of `Lwt_main.run` or any async primitives.

## Implementation Notes

Analogous to `src/main_min.ml` which provides a stripped build. The WASM entrypoint avoids `Unix` module beyond `Sys.argv`, `stdin`, `stdout`. File I/O uses `open_in`/`open_out` from stdlib. The `identity` command reads `AGENTS.md` via `try open_in "AGENTS.md" with Sys_error _ -> ...`. Follow the dispatch pattern in `PLAN_P2_09_WASM_RUNTIME.md` section "Simpler Alternative: WASM Shim".

## Acceptance Criteria

Done when:
- `src/main_wasm.ml` compiles with `dune build src/main_wasm.bc` (bytecode target, no wasm_of_ocaml needed).
- Running `./main_wasm.bc help` prints a help text that mentions all supported commands.
- Running `./main_wasm.bc version` prints a string containing `"wasm"`.
- Running `./main_wasm.bc unknown` exits with code 1.
- `make test` passes (no regressions in existing tests).
